column1: # This is a sample 'constants' file corresponding to the data in the accompanying DGImportTemplate sheet.  A constants file like this one must contain an Xpaths header row
# in Row 1, and a single series of corresponding values in Row 2.   All other information in the worksheet should have a leading hashtag (#) so that it is
# The import process appends the Xpath headers from Row 1 to the Xpaths defined in the import data, and it appends the values from Row 2 to each object (each row) of
# imported data.  Xpaths contained in the constants worksheet should NOT be repeated in the import data!
# When you are ready to import data be sure you save your constants in the same format (TSV or CSV) as the data!
# See the directions provided in DGImportTemplate for more information.
